<h>Iching Reading</h1>

<%= lines %>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th colspan="3"></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>

  <tbody>
  <br>
<b>Your Question was:</b> <%= Ask.last["question"] %><br>
Your Iching reading will consist of 6 lines. Each line is create by flipping a coin 3 times. There are four possible results for each line "Pure Yin", "Pure Yang", "Changing Yin" or "Changing Yang". <br>
The six lines will form a hexagram which can take on one of 64 different forms. Each of the 64 hexagrams has a unique name and meaning.<br>
Here is your Iching hexagram:<br>
<b>Your hexagram number is:</b> <%= Hex.find(hexagram hex_line_name)["hex_id"] %><br>
<b>Hexagram Name:</b> <%= Hex.find(hexagram hex_line_name)["name"] %><br>
<b>Hexagram Meaning:</b> <%= Hex.find(hexagram hex_line_name)["meaning"] %><br>
<b>Hexagram Keywords:</b> <%= Hex.find(hexagram hex_line_name)["keywords"] %><br>
<b>Hexagram Symbols:</b> <%= Hex.find(hexagram hex_line_name)["symbol"] %><br>
<b>Top Trigram:</b> <%= Hex.find(hexagram hex_line_name)["top"] %><br>
<b>Bottom Trigram</b> <%= Hex.find(hexagram hex_line_name)["bottom"] %><br>
<b>Your Changing Line(s)</b> <%= if changing_lines[0].to_i >= 1 and changing_lines[0].to_i < 6 
				    'Your Changed line is ';changing_lines[0]
				  else
				  changing_lines 
				  end%><br>
<b>Your Transformed hexagram number is:</b> <%= Hex.find(transformed_hex)["hex_id"] %><br>
<b> Your Transformed Hex:</b> <%= Hex.find(transformed_hex)["name"] %><br>
<%= trigram %><br>
<b> Top Trigram:</b>
<%= tri_name @top_tri %><br>
<b> Bottom Trigram:</b>
<%= tri_name @bott_tri %><br>
  </tbody>
</table>

